data.chText: 主持（会议、仪式等）；担任（会议）主席
data.enText: to lead or be in charge of a meeting, ceremony, etc.

data.chText: 他们问我是否会主持委员会会议。
data.enText: They asked if I would preside at the committee meeting.

data.chText: 该党执政时期，国家经历了历史上最严重的经济衰退。
data.enText: The party presided over one of the worst economic declines in the country's history (= it was in power when the decline happened) .

simple_means.memory_skill: pre 前 + sid 坐 + e → 在前面坐 → 主持

value.def: If you preside over a meeting or an event, you are in charge.

example.ex: The PM presided over a meeting of his inner Cabinet...
example.tran: 首相主持了一次核心内阁会议。

example.ex: He presided at the trial of the Maguire Seven...
example.tran: 他主审马圭尔等七人案。

example.ex: The presiding officer ruled that the motion was out of order.
example.tran: 主管官员裁定这项动议不符合议事规程。
